    "FunctionId": "9058f624-873e-4a7b-b628-1b56911646f9",
    "Name": "Repeating sequence for FillPattern",
    "Category": "GeniusLoci.FillPattern",
    "Description": "Select a group of Revit Lines to produce a repeating sequence of angles, origins, shifts, offsets, \r\ndashes and spaces.. \r\nFor patterns that have a lot of blank space, it is possible to add a border.  Just type in the Line Style that you are using if one exists; it doesn\u0027t have to be square.\r\nThe Slope Tolerance governs the available Angle at which the diagonal lines will be corrected. Feel free to increase it, but if a line family exceeds or 30 000 millimeters, the pattern will probably not been seen. \r\nWatch the Slope Tolerance Results to see why a FillPattern doesn\u0027t appear.\r\nArc lines will fail.\r\nBy dcmasten1 on forum.dynamobim.com",
    "Path": "C:\\Users\\najwa\\AppData\\Roaming\\Dynamo\\Dynamo Revit\\3.6\\packages\\Genius Loci\\dyf\\Create Repeating Sequence.dyf",
